parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to jerk, hesitate, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or hesitates when shifting gears
loses power
or fails to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch master cylinder failure can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Concentric slave cylinder failure can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Instrument panel gauge failure can cause the driver to be unaware of critical vehicle information, leading to accidents or breakdowns.
symptoms: All instrument panel gauges illuminate and drop to zero
the seat belt indicators illuminate and chime.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear differential failure can cause the vehicle to lose traction and control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle makes an unusual clicking noise
the vehicle becomes hesitant to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the loss of essential functions, such as speedometer, fuel gauge, and engine temperature gauge, leading to a safety hazard, especially at night or in inclement weather.
symptoms: The instrument panel lights fail to illuminate
all gauges drop to zero
the check engine light illuminates
the airbag light stays on
and the AWD malfunction message displays. The backup lights remain on while in drive
posing a safety hazard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to lurch forward and decelerate randomly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle surges forward
the dash cluster goes dead
and the transmission loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake wear and failure can lead to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distance, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Excessive brake dust
grinding noise
squeaking noise
excessive force required to apply brakes
rear brakes wearing out extremely fast
brake pads depleting totally
brake failure
and increased stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distance, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Whining noise when hitting the brakes
acceleration not responding to efforts to stop
jerking abnormality when depressing the brake pedal
and brake pedal feeling soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with the clutch and brake pedals can cause difficulty shifting gears, reduced stopping power, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feeling soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticking to the floor
clutch pedal not returning to its normal position
and delayed or sudden loss of pressure.
